<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-538] when streaming sstables to other nodes, make sure they don&apos;t get compacted before they are streamed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-538</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;at one point (pre-ASF codebase?) this was handled with a bootstrap data dir, but anticompaction no longer puts files there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;at this point it&apos;s probably easier to just make sure streaming keeps a reference to the sstable objects, which will keep them from being deleted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
