                            <comment id="12776551" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 11 Nov 2009 18:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;done as described.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;also adds &quot;not null iterator&quot; to anticompaction similar to the one used in regular compaction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12776795" author="junrao" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2009 02:15:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In CFS.doFileAntiCompaction, why do you need to wrap a FilterIterator with a notNullPredicate over the CompactionIterator? The CompactionIterator never returns null, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12776799" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2009 02:21:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it returns null if either the row had a tombstone that no longer needs to be kept, or if there was a recoverable error (recoverable meaning we can skip to the next row)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12777039" author="junrao" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2009 16:15:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch looks good then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12777279" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2009 23:37:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12777481" author="hudson" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2009 12:35:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #257 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/257/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/257/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    r/m unused bootstrap directory and ensure streaming files live to be streamed&lt;br/&gt;
patch by jbellis; reviewed by Jun Rao for &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
